■ Math Rendering

The sign flip cancels: (-𝑔ₓ)ᶜ mod 𝑁 = (𝑁 - 𝑔ₓ)ᶜ mod 𝑁 = (-1)ᶜ · 𝑔ₓᶜ mod
𝑁.

Inline math like 𝑥² + 𝑦² = 𝑧², magnitudes like ≈ 9.2 × 10¹⁸, the group
(ℤ/𝑛ℤ)* and δ · ⌊15/8⌋ all convert, as do keys such as pkₐ = 𝑔^(skₐ) -
pkᵥ.

Fractions (𝑎+𝑏)/2, roots √2, congruences 𝑎 ≡ 𝑏 (mod 𝑁), sets {1, 3, 5}
and escaped delimiters 𝑎 ≤ 𝑏 work too.

